      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically superlative example of the marque\u2019s water-cooled evolution. At its heart is the 3.6L M96/03 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus, delivering a seamless torque curve and visceral throttle response. This unit features a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent RMS replacement, ensuring long-term reciprocating assembly integrity. The 6-speed G96 manual transaxle provides short, rhythmic throws with perfect synchromesh engagement. The chassis maintains factory-spec rigidity, supported by a multi-link rear suspension that eliminates toe-steer for surgical cornering precision. Finished in original paint with zero oxidation on the undercarriage, this vehicle represents a turnkey opportunity for the collector seeking peak mechanical performance and aesthetic perfection.",
